#week-title("One", "The Seven Metals & Seven Planets: Full Correspondence")

=== Core Teaching

The seven classical metals are not merely chemical substances — they are the
most fully crystallised, most perfectly fixed expressions of the seven planetary
forces within the mineral kingdom. Each metal is the planetary force at its
point of maximum condensation: the moment where the volatile principle has been
so completely fixed by the earth's transforming action over geological time that
it has become a dense, reflective, malleable solid.

*The correspondences:*

