*Metal as crystallised planetary force.* The PRS Bulletins describe each
metallic substance as having a spiritual counterpart manifesting simultaneously,
in accordance with the law of duality. The physical metal and its planetary
archetype are two aspects of the same reality at different degrees of
coagulation. When the practitioner works with lead, they are working with the
Saturn force in its most fixed expression. When they work with gold, they are
working with the Sun force at its point of mineral perfection.

*The alchemical goal: the relationship between lead and gold.* Saturn-lead
represents matter at its heaviest and most crystallised — the prima materia of
the mineral kingdom in its least refined form. Gold represents the same matter
at its highest degree of perfection. The entire arc of metallic alchemy is the
work of understanding and eventually facilitating this transition: from the
heaviness and darkness of lead to the incorruptible luminosity of gold.

=== Topics This Week

- The seven metals and their planetary rulers: full correspondence table
- Metal as crystallised planetary force: the physical and spiritual dual nature
- Lead and Saturn as the beginning; Gold and the Sun as the goal
- The law of duality: physical metal and planetary archetype as one substance

#inner-work[
  *The Planetary Body Scan*

  Sit quietly. As you breathe, bring awareness to each region of the body
  associated with one of the seven metals (using the table above). Beginning
  with the Spleen (Saturn/Lead) and ending with the Heart (Sun/Gold), spend
  one minute at each region simply noticing what is present there.

  Is one region more alive than others? More contracted? Record what you notice
  about the planetary forces as they manifest in your own body.
]

